data.title: Primerica HBI™ data shows middle-income purchasing power steady in Sept. HBI™ at 100.4%, up 0.2% from last month and 0.6% from last year.
data.description: In Duluth, Ga., the most recent Primerica Household Budget Index™ (HBI™) data showed a reading of 100.4% for September. This index, which assesses how inflation and wage patterns affect middle-income families' ability to meet daily expenses, has increased by 0.2% from the previous month and 0.6% from last year. The Consumer Price Index (CPI), a gauge of inflation for a wide range of goods for all U.S. households, saw a 3.0% rise in September compared to the previous year.
